# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Common Commands
- Build: Use `./git_setup.sh` to configure the repository
- Lint: Run `./lint.sh` (if script exists - check .claude directory for customization)
- Test: Execute `./test.sh` (check GuimmSimilarity directory for test suites)
- Run development server: `cd GuimmSimilarity && npm start`

## Code Architecture
- The core functionality resides in the `GuimmSimilarity` directory
- Configuration files are maintained in the `.claude` directory
- Git operations are managed through custom scripts in the root directory

## Key Files
- `guimm-similarity.js`: Main implementation file
- `.aider.*` files: Store interaction history for developer context
- `git_clone.sh`/`git_setup.sh`: Repository initialization scripts

## Configuration Tips
- Customize linting rules in `.claude/settings.json`
- Add new commands to `.claude/hooks/` directory
- Update `.aider.input.history` when refining workflows